sql:
SELECT COUNT(control_point_id) AS active_control_points
FROM control_points
WHERE status = 'active';

SELECT control_point_id
FROM control_points
WHERE station_id = 'A001';

SELECT COUNT(*) 
FROM infrastructure 
WHERE status = 'active';

external_knowledge:
- "peaks" refers to control points;
- "frequently climbed" implies control points that have been accessed more than five times;
- "currently welcoming hikers" means the status of the control point is 'active'.

